---
description: Purity contract for detection functions
globs: "app/detection/**"
---

Functions in `app/detection/` must be pure:

- Signature: `(reading: Reading, history: list[Reading], peers: dict[str, Reading] | None = None) -> list[Event]`.
- No database access. No HTTP calls. No `datetime.now()`, no `time.time()`.
- No mutable module-level state. Constants and lookup tables are fine.
- No `print()`. Detection should not produce side effects.

This contract exists so detection logic is deterministic and testable from a fixed sequence of
readings. Any code suggestion that violates this contract must be revised.
